text: "Supposed to" is an adjective while "suppose" is a verb.
The meeting was supposed to start at 9.
I suppose we'll be starting late.
He was supposed to sing tonight, but he isn't going to.
I suppose he isn't feeling well.
You're supposed to stop for pedestrians at crosswalks.
I suppose some drivers aren't following traffic rules.
She was not supposed to come here.
I suppose she thinks I wouldn't mind.
You weren't supposed to eat so much.
I suppose the food was that delicious.
